Sentencas: A bi-layer interconnect with La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 and La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.6Mn0.4O3 (LSM/LSTM) is applied to anode-supported button cells and flat-tubular cells.
Titulo: Stable LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect for flat-tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using a button cell, SEM images and gas permeation tests confirm that the bi-layer possesses a dense microstructure.
Titulo: Stable LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect for flat-tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of the LSM/LSTM remains nearly constant under oxidizing/reducing atmospheres with varying gas concentrations.
Titulo: Stable LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect for flat-tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For comparison, an LSM/LST with the same thickness is prepared; an increase in the ASR is observed as the concentration of H-2 feed to the LST side decreases.
Titulo: Stable LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect for flat-tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The difference in the ASR of LSM/LST can be explained by exposure to a relatively high oxygen partial pressure and partial destruction of the interfacial LST layer region where oxygen diffuses from the LSM layer.
Titulo: Stable LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect for flat-tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Flat-tubular cells with the LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect achieve a maximum power density (MPD) of 463 mW cm(-2) using humidified H-2 fuel and air at 800 degrees C. With decreasing H-2 concentration in the fuel, the polarization resistance increases rather than the ohmic resistance, implying that the LSM/LSTM interconnect provides stable conduction property.
Titulo: Stable LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect for flat-tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In comparison with the conventional LSM/LST interconnect cell, it shows improved stability and performance as the concentration of H-2 in the fuel decreases.
Titulo: Stable LSM/LSTM bi-layer interconnect for flat-tubular solid oxide fuel cells
